label.value: plasma membrane part of cell-substrate junction.

definition.value: The part of the plasma membrane that contributes to the structure of a cell-substrate junction.
The part of the plasma membrane that contributes to the structure of a hemidesmosome.

label.value: plasma membrane part of cell junction

definition.value: The part of the plasma membrane that contributes to the structure of a cell junction.

A membrane-bound intermediate cleavage-stage structure of individual or groups of chromosomes that coalesces and fuses with other karyomeres to form a nucleus during interphase. Karyomere formation occurs in blastomeres undergoing rapid cell division.
Catalysis of the reaction L-Ala-gamma - -D-Glu-meso-Dap (murein tripeptide) + H2O -eq- L-Ala--and-gamma - -D-Glu + meso-diaminopimelate.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a phagolysosome.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cysteine sulfanate + GTP + IMP -eq- sulfinylpropanyl adenylate + GDP + 3 H(+) + phosphate.

Catalysis of the transfer of fructose from one side of a membrane to the other. In high-affinity transport the transporter is able to bind the solute even if it is only present at very low concentrations.

label.value: central plaque of mitotic spindle pole body

definition.value: One of three laminate structures that form the mitotic spindle pole body -  the central plaque is embedded in the nuclear envelope.

label.value: gamma-tubulin large complex, mitotic spindle pole body

definition.value: A complex of gamma tubulin and associated proteins thought to be formed by multimerization of gamma-tubulin small complexes located in the mitotic spindle pole body.

label.value: gamma-tubulin small complex, mitotic spindle pole body

definition.value: A complex composed of two gamma-tubulin molecules and conserved non-tubulin proteins located in the mitotic spindle pole body and isolated by fractionation from cells. The complex, approximately 6S-9S, is analogous to the small complex in animal cells but contains fewer subunits, and is not thought to multimerize into larger functional units, like complexes in those organisms. An example of this structure is found in Saccharomyces cerevisiae.

label.value: half bridge of mitotic spindle pole body

definition.value: Structure adjacent to the plaques of the mitotic spindle pole body.

label.value: inner plaque of mitotic spindle pole body

definition.value: One of three laminate structures that form the mitotic spindle pole body -  the inner plaque is in the nucleus.

label.value: intermediate layer of mitotic spindle pole body

definition.value: Structure between the central and outer plaques of the mitotic spindle pole body.

label.value: outer plaque of mitotic spindle pole body

definition.value: One of three laminate structures that form the mitotic spindle pole body -  the outer plaque is in the cytoplasm.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + GTP -eq- 2 diphosphate + cyclic GMP-AMP.
Catalysis of the ATP-dependent dehydration of t6A to form cyclic t6A.

Catalysis of a DNA topological transformation by transiently cleaving a pair of complementary DNA strands to form a gate through which a second double-stranded DNA segment is passed, after which the severed strands in the first DNA segment are rejoined -  changes the linking number in multiples of 2.

Catalysis of a DNA topological transformation by transiently cleaving a pair of complementary DNA strands to form a gate through which a second double-stranded DNA segment is passed, after which the severed strands in the first DNA segment are rejoined -  product release is not coupled to ATP binding and hydrolysis -  changes the linking number in multiples of 2.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with cyclic-GMP-AMP (cGAMP) cyclic nucleotide.

Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  glucose 6-phosphate(out) + inorganic phosphate(in) -eq- glucose 6-phosphate(in) + inorganic phosphate(out).
Catalysis of the reaction 1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoyl-CoA + H2O -eq- 1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoate + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + 3-demethylubiquinone-n -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + ubiquinone-n.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + 3-demethylubiquinone-6 -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + ubiquinone-6.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + (1,4)-alpha-D-glucosyl(n) -eq- UMP + (1,4)-alpha-D-glucosyl(n)-glucose-1-phosphate.

A protein complex involved in regulation of mRNA processing and apoptosis. It binds to RNA in a sequence-independent manner and is recruited to the EJC prior to or during the splicing process. In humans the core proteins are RNPS1, SAP18 and ACIN1.

label.value: cyclin-dependent protein serine|threonine kinase activator activity

definition.value: Increases the activity of a cyclin-dependent protein serine|threonine kinase.
A protein complex that catalyzes the reaction acyl-CoA + sphingosine -eq- CoA + N-acylsphingosine. In S. cerevisiae it contains three subunits -  lag1, lac1 and lip1.
Hydrolysis of Lys63-Linked ubiquitin unit(s) from a ubiquitinated protein.
Catalyzing the reaction -  acyl-[acyl-carrier-protein] + S-adenosyl-L-methionine --gt- [acyl-carrier- protein] + S-methyl-5'-thioadenosine + N-acyl-L-homoserine lactone.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription by transcription factor localization

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-dependent transcription using a mechanism that involves the localization of a transcription factor.
The chromatin silencing that results in the inhibition of RNA polymerase II-transcribed genes located in the vicinity of tRNA genes.
Catalysis of the reaction sulfoquinovose -eq- 6-deoxy-6-sulfofructose.
Catalysis of the reaction 6-deoxy-6-sulfofructose + ATP -eq- 6-deoxy-6-sulfofructose-1-phosphate + ADP.
Catalysis of the reaction 6-deoxy-6-sulfofructose-1-phosphate -eq- 3-sulfolactaldehyde + dihydroxyacetone phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction 2,3-dihydroxypropane-1-sulfonate + NAD+ -eq- 3-sulfolactaldehyde + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction GTP -eq- cyclic pyranopterin phosphate + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction ATP + molybdopterin -eq- diphosphate + adenylyl-molybdopterin.
Catalysis of the reaction adenylyl-molybdopterin + molybdate -eq- molybdenum cofactor + AMP.
Catalysis of the reaction CTP + molybdenum cofactor -eq- diphosphate + cytidylyl molybdenum cofactor.
Catalysis of the reaction GTP + molybdenum cofactor -eq- diphosphate + guanylyl molybdenum cofactor.

Catalysis of the reaction -  [Molybdopterin-synthase sulfur-carrier protein]-Gly-Gly-AMP + [cysteine desulfurase]-S-sulfanyl-L-cysteine -lt--eq--gt- AMP [molybdopterin-synthase sulfur-carrier protein]-Gly-NH-CH(2)-C(O)SH + cysteine desulfurase.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP [molybdopterin-synthase sulfur-carrier protein]-Gly-Gly -eq- diphosphate [molybdopterin-synthase sulfur-carrier protein]-Gly-Gly-AMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  propionyl-CoA + peptide -eq- CoA + N-alpha-propionylpeptide. This reaction is the propionylation of the N-terminal amino acid residue of a peptide or protein.
Combining with a nuclear import signal (NIS) to mediate transport of the NIS-containing protein through the nuclear pore to the nucleus.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-fructose-1-phosphate -eq- dihydroxyacetone phosphate + D-glyceraldehyde.

Mitochondrial inner membrane complex involved in maintenance of crista junctions, inner membrane architecture, and formation of contact sites to the outer membrane. In Saccharomyces cerevisiae the complex has six subunits -  MIC10, MIC12, MIC19, MIC26, MIC27, and MIC60.
The part of the basement membrane that lies beneath the lamina densa, containing anchoring fibrils, anchoring plaques, collagen fibers, and elastic fibers.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-methyl-L-methionine + L-homocysteine -eq- 2 L-methionine + H+.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a histone H3 in which the lysine residue at position 27 has been modified by trimethylation.
